(71187, 206644, 0, 1, 'New Year\\''s Day', '', '2009-01-01 00:00:00', 2009, 19, 0, 1, '1,2,3,4!\nIt seemed like only yesterday all our skeletons were found\nWe were living off hysteria, with warm hearts in our hands\nThe television painted pictures of fortuned other lands\nAnd we danced to the jukebox hand in hand\n\nSeventeen and old\nDidn’t we know it all\nYou stole your mamma’s eyes\nI stole all those August nights\n\nWell it seems like only Yesterday\nChasing dreams we knew were false\nOnce upon a time\nWe danced on velvet tinted skies\nAnd years rolled on\nOne day we might just find the time\nBut until then\nWe’ll wait and wonder what happens on New Years Day\n\nI find myself from time to time asking all the right questions\nWho what where when why and how did I become this very person?\nAnd is it all to very late to change your expectations?\nThis time, your time may just have come for you to face the answers\n\nSeventeen and young\nHell those times were fun\nYou loved those old time songs\nI always sang them wrong\n\nWell it seems like only Yesterday\nChasing dreams we knew were false\nOnce upon a time\nWe danced on velvet tinted skies\nAnd years rolled on\nOne day we might just find the time\nBut until then\nWe’ll wait and wonder what happens on New Years Day\n\nSlow Down\n\nWell it seems like only Yesterday\nChasing dreams we knew were false\nOnce upon a time\nWe danced on velvet tinted skies\nAnd years rolled on\nOne day we might just find the time\nBut until then\nWe’ll wait and wonder what happens on New Years Day\n', '', 208, '', '', '', '', 'Shotgun Politics', '', 0, 1, 0, '2014-01-24 02:55:02', '2015-03-12 14:04:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(71188, 56320, 0, 1, 'The Shipwreck\\''s Salvaged Flare', '', '2012-12-13 00:00:00', 2000, 19, 2, 6, 'With the sprinkle star sky aflame\nFrom the shipwreck’s salvaged flare,\nHe could see salvation on the beach\n- Just standing there –\nAnd he waited for their hands to meet.\n\nAnd as he beckoned the waves\nTo wash away his fears,\nHe stood there with the light\nShimmering from his tears.\nAnd the water came\nAnd soothed his feet\nFrom the long road he had tread.\nNow the only thing for him to do\nWas to start looking, way out, straight ahead.\n\nFor the faces he had seen\nAnd the places he had been,\nOnly held a pocket in his mind any more.\nBut his backpack was empty\nWith room set aside\nFor the future sands of time to reside.\n\nThere were times, sure, when he felt\nThat the gloom had taken over,\nWith the shadows of the forest\nSnatching at his shoulders\n\nThen he was saved\nThen he was saved\nThen he was saved\nThen he was saved\n\nWith the sprinkle star sky aflame\nFrom the shipwreck’s salvaged flare,\nHe could see salvation on the beach\n- Just standing there –\nAnd he waited for their hands to meet.', '', 245, '', '', '', '', '聖保保羅', '', 0, 1, 0, '2014-01-24 11:54:42', '2015-03-12 14:04:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(71189, 56320, 0, 1, 'Paint Peels Away', '', '2013-01-24 00:00:00', 2012, 19, 2, 6, 'There’s so much beauty in dilapidation\nAs the paint peels away\nFrom the lone, redundant railway carriage\nWhose last passenger long since paid their fare.\n\nGoing through the station\nWhen you think you are escaping\nIs a lonely experience for any man\nAnd one I don’t want to be repeating.\n\nSo please listen to me\nWhen I say to you\nThat three months is enough\nTo Stave off the demons\nWhich laid inside your head\nWhen the world was much tougher\nTougher than they’d said.\n\nThere’s so much beauty in disrepair\nThat I couldn''t help but sympathise with your despair\nAs I shattered your lucid dreams of being accepted\nWith the truth of your years gone by\nAnd the way you made nearly everybody who ever tried to be somebody to you;\nYou made them cry.\n\nAnd sorry just doesn''t cut it any more\nAnd I''m sorry but you don’t cut it any more.', '', 191, '', '', '', '', '聖保保羅', '', 0, 1, 0, '2014-01-24 11:56:56', '2015-03-12 14:04:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
